[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 7476,
        "end_time": 9165,
        "text": "There have been many different things"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 9165,
        "end_time": 11095,
        "text": "written and said about marriage."
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 11095,
        "end_time": 13028,
        "text": "From the sweetly inspirational"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 13028,
        "end_time": 15464,
        "text": "to the hilariously cynical."
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 15464,
        "end_time": 17344,
        "text": "But what many of them have in common"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 17344,
        "end_time": 18999,
        "text": "is that they sound like they express"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 18999,
        "end_time": 21046,
        "text": "a universal and timeless truth,"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 21046,
        "end_time": 23862,
        "text": "when in fact nearly everything about marriage,"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 23862,
        "end_time": 25370,
        "text": "from its main purpose"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 25370,
        "end_time": 27578,
        "text": "to the kinds of relationships it covers"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 27578,
        "end_time": 29655,
        "text": "to the rights and responsibilities involved,"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 29655,
        "end_time": 31677,
        "text": "has varied greatly between different eras,"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 31677,
        "end_time": 34597,
        "text": "cultures and social classes."
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 34597,
        "end_time": 36151,
        "text": "So, let&#39;s take a quick look at"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 36151,
        "end_time": 38067,
        "text": "the evolution of marriage."
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 38067,
        "end_time": 39652,
        "text": "Pair bonding and raising children"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 39652,
        "end_time": 41935,
        "text": "is as old as humanity itself."
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 41935,
        "end_time": 44604,
        "text": "With the rise of sedentary agricultural societies"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 44604,
        "end_time": 46519,
        "text": "about 10,000 years ago,"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 46519,
        "end_time": 47891,
        "text": "marriage was also a way"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 47891,
        "end_time": 50122,
        "text": "of securing rights to land and property"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 50122,
        "end_time": 53082,
        "text": "by designating children born under certain circumstances"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 53082,
        "end_time": 55021,
        "text": "as rightful heirs."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 55021,
        "end_time": 57963,
        "text": "As these societies became larger and more complex,"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 57963,
        "end_time": 59880,
        "text": "marriage became not just a matter"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 59880,
        "end_time": 61634,
        "text": "between individuals and families,"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 61634,
        "end_time": 63675,
        "text": "but also an official institution"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 63675,
        "end_time": 66722,
        "text": "governed by religious and civil authorities."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 66722,
        "end_time": 70268,
        "text": "And it was already well established by 2100 B.C."
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 70268,
        "end_time": 72521,
        "text": "when the earliest surviving written laws"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 72521,
        "end_time": 75062,
        "text": "in the Mesopotamian Code of Ur-Nammu"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 75062,
        "end_time": 77521,
        "text": "provided many specifics governing marriage,"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 77521,
        "end_time": 79019,
        "text": "from punishments for adultery"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 79019,
        "end_time": 82771,
        "text": "to the legal status of children born to slaves."
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 82771,
        "end_time": 85103,
        "text": "Many ancient civilizations allowed some form of"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 85103,
        "end_time": 87491,
        "text": "multiple simultaneous marriage."
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 87491,
        "end_time": 89686,
        "text": "And even today, less than a quarter of the world&#39;s"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 89686,
        "end_time": 92495,
        "text": "hundreds of different cultures prohibit it."
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 92495,
        "end_time": 94271,
        "text": "But just because something was allowed"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 94271,
        "end_time": 96672,
        "text": "doesn&#39;t mean it was always possible."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 96672,
        "end_time": 98212,
        "text": "Demographic realities,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 98212,
        "end_time": 100796,
        "text": "as well as the link between marriage and wealth,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 100796,
        "end_time": 102521,
        "text": "meant that even though rulers and elites"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 102521,
        "end_time": 103927,
        "text": "in Ancient Mesopotamia,"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 103927,
        "end_time": 105343,
        "text": "Egypt and Israel"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 105343,
        "end_time": 107637,
        "text": "had multiple concubines or wives,"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 107637,
        "end_time": 110643,
        "text": "most commoners could only afford one or two"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 110643,
        "end_time": 113520,
        "text": "tending towards monogamy in practice."
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 113520,
        "end_time": 115937,
        "text": "In other places, the tables were turned,"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 115937,
        "end_time": 117604,
        "text": "and a woman could have multiple husbands"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 117604,
        "end_time": 119400,
        "text": "as in the Himalayan Mountains"
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 119400,
        "end_time": 120853,
        "text": "where all brothers in a family"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 120853,
        "end_time": 122186,
        "text": "marrying the same woman"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 122186,
        "end_time": 123937,
        "text": "kept the small amount of fertile land"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 123937,
        "end_time": 127271,
        "text": "from being constantly divided into new households."
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 127271,
        "end_time": 128407,
        "text": "Marriages could vary"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 128407,
        "end_time": 130351,
        "text": "not only in the number of people they involved"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 130351,
        "end_time": 132604,
        "text": "but the types of people as well."
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 132604,
        "end_time": 134833,
        "text": "Although the names and laws for such arrangements"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 134833,
        "end_time": 135830,
        "text": "may have differed,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 135830,
        "end_time": 138103,
        "text": "publicly recognized same-sex unions"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 138103,
        "end_time": 139209,
        "text": "have popped up"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 139209,
        "end_time": 141753,
        "text": "in various civilizations throughout history."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 141753,
        "end_time": 145006,
        "text": "Mesopotamian prayers included blessings for such couples,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 145006,
        "end_time": 147604,
        "text": "while Native American Two-Spirit individuals"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 147604,
        "end_time": 150306,
        "text": "had relationships with both sexes."
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 150306,
        "end_time": 152473,
        "text": "The first instances of such arrangements"
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 152473,
        "end_time": 153936,
        "text": "actually being called &quot;Marriage&quot;"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 153936,
        "end_time": 155058,
        "text": "come from Rome,"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 155058,
        "end_time": 156937,
        "text": "where the Emperors Nero and Elagabalus"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 156937,
        "end_time": 159520,
        "text": "both married men in public ceremonies"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 159520,
        "end_time": 161520,
        "text": "with the practice being explictly banned"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 161520,
        "end_time": 163686,
        "text": "in 342 A.D."
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 163686,
        "end_time": 165151,
        "text": "But similar traditions survived"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 165151,
        "end_time": 166822,
        "text": "well into the Christian era,"
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 166822,
        "end_time": 168354,
        "text": "such as Adelphopoiesis,"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 168354,
        "end_time": 170854,
        "text": "or &quot;brother-making&quot; in Orthodox churches,"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 170854,
        "end_time": 173103,
        "text": "and even an actual marriage between two men"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 173103,
        "end_time": 177497,
        "text": "recorded in 1061 at a small chapel in Spain."
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 177497,
        "end_time": 179043,
        "text": "Nor was marriage even necessarily"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 179043,
        "end_time": 181254,
        "text": "between two living people."
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 181254,
        "end_time": 182457,
        "text": "Ghost marriages,"
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 182457,
        "end_time": 184213,
        "text": "where either the bride or groom were deceased,"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 184213,
        "end_time": 185546,
        "text": "were conducted in China"
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 185546,
        "end_time": 187468,
        "text": "to continue family lineages"
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 187468,
        "end_time": 189469,
        "text": "or appease restless spirits."
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 189469,
        "end_time": 193389,
        "text": "And some tribes in Sudan maintain similar practices."
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 193389,
        "end_time": 194807,
        "text": "Despite all these differences,"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 194807,
        "end_time": 196435,
        "text": "a lot of marriages throughout history"
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 196435,
        "end_time": 198896,
        "text": "did have one thing in common."
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 198896,
        "end_time": 199854,
        "text": "With crucial matters"
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 199854,
        "end_time": 201853,
        "text": "like property and reproduction at stake,"
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 201853,
        "end_time": 203354,
        "text": "they were way too important"
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 203354,
        "end_time": 205655,
        "text": "to depend on young love."
    },
    {
        "index": 95,
        "start_time": 205655,
        "end_time": 207520,
        "text": "Especially among the upperclasses,"
    },
    {
        "index": 96,
        "start_time": 207520,
        "end_time": 210824,
        "text": "matches were often made by families or rulers."
    },
    {
        "index": 97,
        "start_time": 210824,
        "end_time": 213436,
        "text": "But even for commoners, who had some degree of choice,"
    },
    {
        "index": 98,
        "start_time": 213436,
        "end_time": 215597,
        "text": "the main concern was practicality."
    },
    {
        "index": 99,
        "start_time": 215597,
        "end_time": 217581,
        "text": "The modern idea of marriage"
    },
    {
        "index": 100,
        "start_time": 217581,
        "end_time": 220104,
        "text": "as being mainly about love and companionship"
    },
    {
        "index": 101,
        "start_time": 220104,
        "end_time": 222916,
        "text": "only emerged in the last couple of centuries."
    },
    {
        "index": 102,
        "start_time": 222916,
        "end_time": 224214,
        "text": "With industrialization,"
    },
    {
        "index": 103,
        "start_time": 224214,
        "end_time": 225212,
        "text": "urbanization"
    },
    {
        "index": 104,
        "start_time": 225212,
        "end_time": 226923,
        "text": "and the growth of the middle class"
    },
    {
        "index": 105,
        "start_time": 226923,
        "end_time": 228381,
        "text": "more people became independent"
    },
    {
        "index": 106,
        "start_time": 228381,
        "end_time": 230186,
        "text": "from large extended families"
    },
    {
        "index": 107,
        "start_time": 230186,
        "end_time": 231187,
        "text": "and were able to support"
    },
    {
        "index": 108,
        "start_time": 231187,
        "end_time": 233050,
        "text": "a new household on their own."
    },
    {
        "index": 109,
        "start_time": 233050,
        "end_time": 234520,
        "text": "Encouraged by new ideas"
    },
    {
        "index": 110,
        "start_time": 234520,
        "end_time": 235686,
        "text": "from the Enlightenment,"
    },
    {
        "index": 111,
        "start_time": 235686,
        "end_time": 236808,
        "text": "people began to focus"
    },
    {
        "index": 112,
        "start_time": 236808,
        "end_time": 239269,
        "text": "on individual happiness and pursuits,"
    },
    {
        "index": 113,
        "start_time": 239269,
        "end_time": 242229,
        "text": "rather than familial duty or wealth and status,"
    },
    {
        "index": 114,
        "start_time": 242229,
        "end_time": 243531,
        "text": "at least some of the time."
    },
    {
        "index": 115,
        "start_time": 243531,
        "end_time": 245652,
        "text": "And this focus on individual happiness"
    },
    {
        "index": 116,
        "start_time": 245652,
        "end_time": 248187,
        "text": "soon led to other transformations,"
    },
    {
        "index": 117,
        "start_time": 248187,
        "end_time": 250322,
        "text": "such as easing restrictions on divorce"
    },
    {
        "index": 118,
        "start_time": 250322,
        "end_time": 252989,
        "text": "and more people marrying at a later age."
    },
    {
        "index": 119,
        "start_time": 252989,
        "end_time": 255688,
        "text": "So, as we continue to debate the role and definition"
    },
    {
        "index": 120,
        "start_time": 255688,
        "end_time": 257271,
        "text": "of marriage in the modern world,"
    },
    {
        "index": 121,
        "start_time": 257271,
        "end_time": 258622,
        "text": "it might help to keep in mind"
    },
    {
        "index": 122,
        "start_time": 258622,
        "end_time": 261270,
        "text": "that marriage has always been shaped by society,"
    },
    {
        "index": 123,
        "start_time": 261270,
        "end_time": 262291,
        "text": "and as a society&#39;s"
    },
    {
        "index": 124,
        "start_time": 262291,
        "end_time": 264103,
        "text": "structure, values and goals"
    },
    {
        "index": 125,
        "start_time": 264103,
        "end_time": 265196,
        "text": "change over time,"
    },
    {
        "index": 126,
        "start_time": 265196,
        "end_time": 268811,
        "text": "its ideas of marriage will continue to change along with them."
    }
]